While the btc cools off a little bit , i have my eyes on dao and nfts projects.
In DAOs, governance tokens can be easily purchased on exchanges. This means that if an individual has enough money, he/she can effectively purchase all the voting rights. This accumulation of voting power would grant too much authority to a single organisation, creating a massive gap for any investment body to exploit the governance in exchange for money.
SpiderDAO fights against these faults by separating the governance token from voting rights. Instead, SpiderDAO requires users to have a compatible Spider Router installed and stake SPDR governance tokens in order to receive voting rights. One Spider Router installed would equate to 1 voting rights. SPDR token would be used for utility purposes. Moreover, SPDR tokens can be used for “liquidity as utility” services and liquidity mining - quite similar to the DeFi model.
